<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_cadæg" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>cadæg</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>тихий</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>медленный</q></cit></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cadæggaj</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>понемногу</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>little by little</q></cit></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_cadæg." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>cadæggaj jyl abady (bæxyl)</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>потихоньку садится (на коня)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>[s/he] is mounting a horse little by little</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 139</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>cadæggaj jyl abady (bæxyl)</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>потихоньку садится (на коня)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>[s/he] is mounting a horse little by little</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV 139</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Прош. причастик от глагола *%icajyn%i, снабженное суффиксом %iæg%i (%icad-æg%i = <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyāta-ka</w></mentioned>). Глагол *%icajyn%i (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyā-</w><gloss><q>покоиться</q></gloss></mentioned> сохранился только в сращении с превербом %iæn%i-: <xr><ref target="#entry_æncajyn"/></xr> : <xr><ref target="#entry_æncad"/></xr> ‘покоиться’. Такую же морфологическую структуру, как %icadæg%i (прош. причастие + %iæg%i), имеют <xr><ref target="#entry_syǧdæg"/></xr> ‘чистый’, <xr><ref target="#entry_lystæg"/></xr> ‘мелкий’, <xr><ref target="#entry_cærdæg"/></xr> ‘живой’ и др. У поэта <bibl><author>Коста</author></bibl> (в черновых рукописях) встречается также форма %iæncadæg%i. Взятое без суффикса -%iæg%i осетинское <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>cad-</w></mentioned> точно соответствует <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>šāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>šāt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>šād</w><gloss><q>радостный</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. См. <xr><ref target="#entry_æncajyn"/><ref target="#entry_æncad"/><ref target="#entry_æncoj"/><ref target="#entry_æncon"/></xr>.%n<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Past participle form of the verb %icajyn%i with the suffix %iæg%i (%icad-æg%i = <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyāta-ka</w></mentioned>). The verb *%icajyn%i (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyā-</w><gloss><q>repose</q></gloss></mentioned> remained only bound with the preverb %iæn%i-: <xr><ref target="#entry_æncajyn"/></xr> : <xr><ref target="#entry_æncad"/></xr> ‘repose’. The same morphological structure, as %icadæg%i (past participle + %iæg%i), is found in <xr><ref target="#entry_syǧdæg"/></xr> ‘pure’, <xr><ref target="#entry_lystæg"/></xr> ‘small’, <xr><ref target="#entry_cærdæg"/></xr> ‘alive’ etc. The poet <bibl><author>Kosta</author></bibl> had (in drafts) the form %iæncadæg%i. The Ossetic word <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>cad-</w></mentioned> without suffix -%iæg%i exactly corresponds <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>čyāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>šāta-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>šāt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>šād</w><gloss><q>happy</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. See <xr><ref target="#entry_æncajyn"/><ref target="#entry_æncad"/><ref target="#entry_æncoj"/><ref target="#entry_æncon"/></xr>.%n<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>